Philippine: The Society of Jesus in the Philippines is expelled by Raón after receiving a dated later from Charles III's chief minister Don Pedro Pablo Abarca de Bolea on March 1, 1767. The Jesuit's Properties are confiscated by the Spanish Colonial Government
Nepal: Conquest of Chaudandi and Majh Kirant states.
Indonesia: French expeditions capture clove plants in Ambon, ending the VOC monopoly of the plant. (to 1772)
East_Timor: The capital was moved to Dili.
